00:41:54,567 --> 00:41:58,230
KAB 1340.

459
00:42:00,240 --> 00:42:02,071
Fifty-seven.

460
00:42:05,545 --> 00:42:07,979
From the top of the world...

461
00:42:08,014 --> 00:42:11,074
fabulous 1340.

462
00:42:11,117 --> 00:42:14,678
KAB, Antonio Bay.

463
00:42:16,789 --> 00:42:18,279
Thirty-one.

464
00:42:20,126 --> 00:42:24,085
From the top of the world,
fabulous 1340.

465
00:42:24,130 --> 00:42:30,933
The smooth sound of KAB,
Antonio Bay, California.

466
00:42:33,373 --> 00:42:35,739
Fifty-four.

467
00:42:35,775 --> 00:42:40,007
KAB 1340.

468
00:42:43,950 --> 00:42:46,282
Thirty-one.

469
00:42:46,319 --> 00:42:50,551
The sounds of the surf
from Antonio Bay.

470
00:42:50,590 --> 00:42:54,219
KAB 1340.

471
00:42:57,063 --> 00:42:58,325
Thirty-nine.

472
00:42:58,364 --> 00:43:04,234
Fabulous 1340,
KAB, Antonio Bay.

473
00:43:08,575 --> 00:43:14,411
More music on
top of the world, KAB 1340.

474
00:43:18,918 --> 00:43:23,412
EST-111-B, cut two.

475
00:43:25,091 --> 00:43:26,558
From the top of the world...

476
00:43:26,593 --> 00:43:31,030
fabulous 1340 KAB,
Antonio Bay.

477
00:43:33,733 --> 00:43:36,793
Father, where did you find this?

478
00:43:36,836 --> 00:43:40,533
My grandfather hid his sins
in the walls.

479
00:43:40,573 --> 00:43:43,041
When did you find it?

480
00:43:43,076 --> 00:43:46,204
Last night,
just after midnight.

481
00:43:46,246 --> 00:43:48,077
What difference does it make?

482
00:43:48,114 --> 00:43:50,947
That's the same time
the rest of the town fell apart.

483
00:43:55,755 --> 00:43:59,054
And the same time
the six conspirators met...

484
00:43:59,092 --> 00:44:01,492
one hundred years ago.

485
00:44:01,527 --> 00:44:03,654
It's really getting late.

486
00:44:03,696 --> 00:44:06,392
There's not much we can do
about any of this.

487
00:44:06,432 --> 00:44:10,129
Are you going to give
the benediction tonight, Father?

488
00:44:10,169 --> 00:44:13,570
Antonio Bay has a curse on it.

489
00:44:13,606 --> 00:44:15,540
Do we take that as a ''no''?

490
00:44:15,575 --> 00:44:17,770
Maybe it's just as well.

491
00:44:20,213 --> 00:44:23,182
We're leaving now, Father.

492
00:44:23,216 --> 00:44:25,241
Will you be all right?

493
00:44:27,920 --> 00:44:33,256
I'm going to call Dr. Thayden
and ask him to just drop by.

494
00:44:33,293 --> 00:44:36,319
I think you're taking
all of this much too seriously.

495
00:44:36,362 --> 00:44:39,923
We're all cursed,
Mrs. Williams...

496
00:44:39,966 --> 00:44:41,593
all of us.

497
00:44:53,813 --> 00:44:59,080
1340 KAB.

498
00:44:59,118 --> 00:45:01,348
Forty-four.

499
00:45:01,387 --> 00:45:08,293
The smooth sound.
Fabulous 1340 KAB.

500
00:45:14,567 --> 00:45:16,558
Forty-five.

501
00:45:16,602 --> 00:45:22,734
From the top of the world,
fabulous 1340 KAB...

502
00:45:22,775 --> 00:45:26,336
Antonio Bay, California.

503
00:45:26,379 --> 00:45:27,903
Forty-six.

504
00:45:29,082 --> 00:45:31,550
The smooth sound...

505
00:45:33,052 --> 00:45:37,216
Something like
an albatross around the neck...

506
00:45:37,256 --> 00:45:39,724
No. More like a millstone...

507
00:45:39,759 --> 00:45:42,557
a plumbing stone, by God.

508
00:45:42,595 --> 00:45:44,961
Damn them all!

509
00:46:00,680 --> 00:46:02,671
Nine.
Every hour on the hour...

510
00:46:02,715 --> 00:46:04,945
KAB news and weather.

511
00:46:04,984 --> 00:46:06,747
Ten.

512
00:46:06,786 --> 00:46:11,883
Every hour on the hour,
KAB news and weather.

513
00:46:14,227 --> 00:46:17,458
End side two, KAB promos.

514
00:46:28,174 --> 00:46:31,701
How can a man drown
and not touch the water?

515
00:46:31,744 --> 00:46:34,372
He had water in his lungs...

516
00:46:34,414 --> 00:46:38,145
salt water around his mouth,
seaweed in his clothes.

517
00:46:38,184 --> 00:46:40,209
Unless...

518
00:46:42,922 --> 00:46:44,981
You OK?

519
00:46:45,024 --> 00:46:47,891
Did you see his eyes?

520
00:46:47,927 --> 00:46:50,088
Yeah, I saw his eyes.

521
00:46:57,403 --> 00:47:00,236
Andy, the telephone.

522
00:47:00,273 --> 00:47:02,207
I got it, Mrs. Kobritz.

523
00:47:07,647 --> 00:47:09,512
Andy, where did you get
that piece of driftwood?

524
00:47:09,549 --> 00:47:12,143
I told you, Mom.
On the beach this morning.

525
00:47:12,185 --> 00:47:13,675
- Where?
- By the rocks.

526
00:47:13,719 --> 00:47:15,118
What was it doing?

527
00:47:15,154 --> 00:47:17,122
First it was a gold coin...

528
00:47:17,156 --> 00:47:19,249
and then it turned
into the wood.

529
00:47:19,292 --> 00:47:21,351
Andy, I want you
to stay away from the rocks.

530
00:47:21,394 --> 00:47:22,520
Do you understand?

531
00:47:22,562 --> 00:47:24,860
Don't pick up anything else
off the beach.

532
00:47:24,897 --> 00:47:26,364
It didn't belong to anybody.

533
00:47:26,399 --> 00:47:28,026
I know, honey.
It's all right.

534
00:47:28,067 --> 00:47:29,864
I just don't want you
to pick up anything else...

535
00:47:29,902 --> 00:47:31,995
unless you come
and get me first. OK?

536
00:47:32,038 --> 00:47:33,801
OK.

537
00:47:33,840 --> 00:47:35,705
Is Mrs. Kobritz there?

538
00:47:35,741 --> 00:47:37,709
She just came in.

539
00:47:37,743 --> 00:47:42,146
OK. I have to start
the broadcast now.

540
00:47:42,181 --> 00:47:44,581
Andy, promise me you won't
leave the house tonight.

541
00:47:44,617 --> 00:47:46,380
Oh, Mom.

542
00:47:46,419 --> 00:47:48,546
Promise me.

543
00:47:48,588 --> 00:47:50,954
Oh, OK.

544
00:47:50,990 --> 00:47:53,151
I love you, Andy.

545
00:47:53,192 --> 00:47:55,524
Me, too, Mom. Bye.

546
00:48:22,555 --> 00:48:24,216
Ahoy, maties.

547
00:48:24,257 --> 00:48:27,590
This is Stevie Wayne,
your night light...

548
00:48:27,627 --> 00:48:32,587
and KAB, Antonio Bay,
California, is on the air.

549
00:48:32,632 --> 00:48:34,930
I've lined up some tunes
to help you celebrate...

550
00:48:34,967 --> 00:48:37,800
the 100th birthday
of Antonio Bay.

551
00:48:37,837 --> 00:48:41,739
So let's get down to business.

552
00:49:03,095 --> 00:49:05,222
What did your mother want, Andy?

553
00:49:05,264 --> 00:49:06,663
Nothing.

554
00:49:06,699 --> 00:49:08,929
It must have been something.

555
00:49:08,968 --> 00:49:11,562
Nothing.

556
00:49:11,604 --> 00:49:15,040
Mrs. Kobritz,
what are those clouds out there?

557
00:49:21,881 --> 00:49:23,644
Evidence of deep
penetrating wounds...

558
00:49:23,683 --> 00:49:25,173
in each ocular orbit...

559
00:49:25,217 --> 00:49:27,685
entering into
the cranial cavity.

560
00:49:27,720 --> 00:49:30,245
Also jagged lacerations
to the face...

561
00:49:30,289 --> 00:49:31,950
Do you want to wait out front?

562
00:49:31,991 --> 00:49:33,856
I'd rather wait with you.

563
00:49:33,893 --> 00:49:35,258
OK.

564
00:49:35,294 --> 00:49:37,285
Thorax has been crushed...

565
00:49:37,330 --> 00:49:40,663
and the lungs
are filled with fluid.

566
00:49:40,700 --> 00:49:41,860
Talk to you a minute?

567
00:49:49,508 --> 00:49:51,203
She gonna be all right?

568
00:49:51,243 --> 00:49:53,336
- Did you talk to Simms?
- I got him on the radio.

569
00:49:53,379 --> 00:49:55,210
He's coming back
from Bodega Bay.

570
00:49:55,247 --> 00:49:56,714
What the hell
happened out there?

571
00:49:56,749 --> 00:49:58,546
There was rust
all over everything.

572
00:49:58,584 --> 00:50:00,279
It was like the boat had been
out there a long time...

573
00:50:00,319 --> 00:50:01,718
taking on water.

574
00:50:01,754 --> 00:50:03,551
He was down below
near the bunks.

575
00:50:03,589 --> 00:50:05,887
Nick, his wounds
are covered with algae...

576
00:50:05,925 --> 00:50:07,051
his lungs are full...

577
00:50:07,093 --> 00:50:09,118
and there's silt
under his fingernails.

578
00:50:09,161 --> 00:50:12,392
I saw Dick Baxter
three days ago in Salinas.

579
00:50:12,431 --> 00:50:13,796
Now he's lying in there
on the table...

580
00:50:13,833 --> 00:50:16,301
looking like he's been
underwater for a month.

581
00:50:38,791 --> 00:50:41,316
- Do you feel that?
- I'll tell you what happens.

582
00:50:41,360 --> 00:50:44,761
- It just got cold in here.
- The water acts like ice.

583
00:50:55,541 --> 00:50:58,032
A whole body would take a year
to decompose...

584
00:50:58,077 --> 00:51:00,545
longer if it was down
far enough, cold enough.

585
00:51:00,579 --> 00:51:02,376
But he was on the boat.

586
00:51:02,415 --> 00:51:03,814
He was below decks.

587
00:51:03,849 --> 00:51:07,842
No. Dick Baxter
died in the ocean.

588
00:51:23,769 --> 00:51:25,896
You remember those three kids
that went diving...

589
00:51:25,938 --> 00:51:28,270
for that old boat off the Point?

590
00:51:28,307 --> 00:51:30,400
We got to them,
they'd been down for a week...

591
00:51:30,443 --> 00:51:31,569
maybe ten days.

592
00:51:31,610 --> 00:51:35,307
I swear to you right now,
he's been down longer.

593
00:52:58,097 --> 00:53:00,463
And while the wrecking
of that beautiful ship...

594
00:53:00,499 --> 00:53:02,797
upon our coast was,
of course...

595
00:53:02,835 --> 00:53:05,861
a tragedy to those
who were on the ship...

596
00:53:05,905 --> 00:53:09,204
it still was the catalyst
that brought together...

597
00:53:09,241 --> 00:53:12,301
all of the people
of this wonderful area.

598
00:53:12,344 --> 00:53:13,743
They came together...

599
00:53:13,779 --> 00:53:17,180
they formed the charter
for Antonio Bay...

600
00:53:17,216 --> 00:53:20,276
the charter by which you have
voted for these councilmen...

601
00:53:20,319 --> 00:53:22,913
who sit on my left
and my right tonight.

602
00:53:24,156 --> 00:53:26,954
The Coast Guard's
looking for them.

603
00:53:26,992 --> 00:53:29,290
They're going to cover the area
pretty good...

604
00:53:29,328 --> 00:53:33,196
so, really,
all we can do is wait.

605
00:53:33,232 --> 00:53:35,393
I understand, Sheriff.

606
00:53:35,434 --> 00:53:36,924
Thank you.

607
00:53:38,704 --> 00:53:40,899
I got to go. I'm up next.

608
00:53:44,076 --> 00:53:46,476
I'm so sorry, Mrs. Williams.

609
00:53:49,515 --> 00:53:52,916
It's funny,
but all I can think about...

610
00:53:52,952 --> 00:53:56,183
is my silly dog
barking all night...

611
00:53:56,222 --> 00:54:01,216
and me just wishing
Al would come home.

612
00:54:03,896 --> 00:54:07,525
Now, we can't have
the chairlady...

613
00:54:07,566 --> 00:54:10,057
of the birthday celebration
in tears, can we?

614
00:54:10,102 --> 00:54:11,535
I don't think you ought
to go out there.

615
00:54:11,570 --> 00:54:15,438
I think that's exactly
what I ought to do.

616
00:54:15,474 --> 00:54:17,704
I appreciate
all your help, Nick.

617
00:54:17,743 --> 00:54:19,074
That's all right.

618
00:54:37,129 --> 00:54:39,620
I searched
a long time for this one.

619
00:54:39,665 --> 00:54:42,031
I hope you remember it.

620
00:54:46,438 --> 00:54:48,235
Happy 100th, Antonio Bay.

621
00:54:48,274 --> 00:54:51,641
The ceremonies are underway
at Shelby Square.

622
00:54:51,677 --> 00:54:54,578
And we'll have that candlelight
procession in about an hour.

623
00:54:54,613 --> 00:54:58,344
So if you hurry,
you can still make it.

624
00:54:58,384 --> 00:54:59,851
The Coast Guard
dropped me a note.

625
00:54:59,885 --> 00:55:02,945
They found the ''Sea Grass''
earlier this afternoon...

626
00:55:02,988 --> 00:55:04,478
but there's no further word...

627
00:55:04,523 --> 00:55:08,357
as to the condition of the ship
or the men on-board.

628
00:55:08,394 --> 00:55:11,727
I'll keep you posted
as the news comes in to me.

629
00:55:11,764 --> 00:55:14,597
Hope no one else gets lost
out there in the fog.

630
00:55:18,837 --> 00:55:20,395
I'll be right back.

631
00:55:30,082 --> 00:55:31,709
Hello. My name's Nick Castle.

632
00:55:31,750 --> 00:55:33,547
You don't know me,
but I'm one of the men...

633
00:55:33,585 --> 00:55:35,485
who found the ''Sea Grass''
this afternoon.

634
00:55:35,521 --> 00:55:37,819
I'm sorry.
I don't have any further word.

635
00:55:37,856 --> 00:55:40,222
I understand.
That's not what I called about.

636
00:55:40,259 --> 00:55:43,990
You just mentioned something
now on the radio about the fog.

637
00:55:52,771 --> 00:55:57,333
This is going to sound
a little strange, but...

638
00:55:57,376 --> 00:55:59,276
I saw the fog last night...

639
00:55:59,311 --> 00:56:00,835
out in the ocean
in the distance.

640
00:56:00,879 --> 00:56:03,677
It was...glowing.

641
00:56:09,822 --> 00:56:10,948
What seemed to be happening...

642
00:56:10,990 --> 00:56:13,015
is that the wind
was moving due east...

643
00:56:13,058 --> 00:56:15,356
and the fog
just kept moving west.

644
00:56:15,394 --> 00:56:16,918
I know that sounds
completely crazy.

645
00:56:16,962 --> 00:56:18,395
Right now it doesn't.

646
00:56:18,430 --> 00:56:20,591
Something happened last night.

647
00:56:20,632 --> 00:56:22,361
At the same time
that fog was moving in...

648
00:56:22,401 --> 00:56:24,392
this whole town went unglued.

649
00:56:24,436 --> 00:56:25,903
Hold on.

650
00:56:29,875 --> 00:56:32,366
I've got some more
birthday music for you...

651
00:56:32,411 --> 00:56:34,276
and a few other surprises.

652
00:56:34,313 --> 00:56:37,578
Then I'll be ready to check in
with the weatherman.

653
00:56:37,616 --> 00:56:41,074
And the weatherman will be
ready to check in with you.

654
00:56:51,897 --> 00:56:53,865
- Hello?
- I'm still here.

655
00:56:53,899 --> 00:56:55,230
There's one other thing.

656
00:56:55,267 --> 00:56:57,997
It may have nothing
to do with the ''Sea Grass''.

657
00:56:58,037 --> 00:57:00,096
Anything.

658
00:57:00,139 --> 00:57:03,870
My son found a piece
of driftwood this morning.

659
00:57:09,715 --> 00:57:12,946
Hey, Mel. How you doing?

660
00:57:12,985 --> 00:57:16,182
Your girlfriend on the radio
has been talking about you.

661
00:57:16,221 --> 00:57:18,189
I came in tonight
just to keep her happy.

662
00:57:18,223 --> 00:57:19,815
I thought
you were off tonight.

663
00:57:19,858 --> 00:57:21,018
I love my job.

664
00:57:21,060 --> 00:57:24,359
You can tell them all
about that big fog bank...

665
00:57:24,396 --> 00:57:26,057
moving in
the southeast there.

666
00:57:26,098 --> 00:57:28,692
- Where?
- You'll see it.

667
00:57:28,734 --> 00:57:30,702
I'm on my way.
See you tomorrow.

668
00:57:30,736 --> 00:57:32,727
Yeah, Mel. I'll see you.

669
00:57:42,614 --> 00:57:44,138
There you are.

670
00:57:54,159 --> 00:57:55,751
I've got to make a run
out to the lighthouse...

671
00:57:55,794 --> 00:57:57,318
at Spivey Point.
Want to come?

672
00:57:57,362 --> 00:57:58,624
- Sure.
- Come on.

673
00:58:04,369 --> 00:58:05,768
Hi, sweetheart!

674
00:58:05,804 --> 00:58:07,032
I thought you were celebrating.

675
00:58:07,072 --> 00:58:09,870
I couldn't spend an evening
without you.

676
00:58:09,908 --> 00:58:12,570
I'm up in about thirty seconds.
What's new?

677
00:58:12,611 --> 00:58:14,772
Another fog bank.

678
00:58:14,813 --> 00:58:16,246
Where?

679
00:58:16,281 --> 00:58:18,545
It's coming in off the ocean
from the southeast.

680
00:58:18,584 --> 00:58:20,347
It's heading inland.
It should be here...

681
00:58:20,385 --> 00:58:22,080
at the weather station
in ten minutes.

682
00:58:22,121 --> 00:58:24,681
Dan, hold on.

683
00:58:26,024 --> 00:58:28,083
I have a special
weather bulletin.

684
00:58:28,127 --> 00:58:29,685
The tri-county
weather station...

685
00:58:29,728 --> 00:58:33,095
reports a fog bank moving
southeast along the coast.

686
00:58:33,132 --> 00:58:34,827
For whoever's interested...

687
00:58:34,867 --> 00:58:38,200
that's the weather station
on Old Russellville Road.

688
00:58:38,237 --> 00:58:42,230
Repeating... a fog bank is moving
southwest along the coast...

689
00:58:42,274 --> 00:58:45,402
toward the weather station
on Old Russellville Road.

690
00:58:50,215 --> 00:58:52,046
Dan, are you still there?

691
00:58:52,084 --> 00:58:54,382
I'm still here.

692
00:58:54,419 --> 00:58:56,444
You sound different tonight...

693
00:58:56,488 --> 00:58:58,513
kind of intense.

694
00:58:58,557 --> 00:59:01,185
I just feel like talking,
that's all.

695
00:59:01,226 --> 00:59:03,524
You told me you didn't like
to talk on the telephone...

696
00:59:03,562 --> 00:59:05,359
because you talked
on the radio all day.

697
00:59:05,397 --> 00:59:06,591
Dan, where's the fog now?

698
00:59:06,632 --> 00:59:09,533
It should be
right outside my door now.

699
00:59:12,704 --> 00:59:14,501
Hold on.
I'm going to try something.

700
00:59:20,078 --> 00:59:21,272
I can see it.

701
00:59:21,313 --> 00:59:24,043
Now, what is the big deal?

702
00:59:24,082 --> 00:59:26,141
You've seen fog once,
you seen it for life.

703
00:59:26,185 --> 00:59:28,210
There's something
different about this fog.

704
00:59:28,253 --> 00:59:31,051
It glows.
Can't you see anything yet?

705
00:59:31,089 --> 00:59:34,547
Glows? Oh, I get it.

706
00:59:34,593 --> 00:59:36,561
You take something
to keep you going, right?

707
00:59:36,595 --> 00:59:39,257
Does it make you feel
a little weird sometimes?

708
00:59:40,432 --> 00:59:43,230
- Hey.
- What?

709
00:59:43,268 --> 00:59:45,236
The lights went out.

710
00:59:45,270 --> 00:59:48,569
Everything's going crazy.

711
00:59:48,607 --> 00:59:51,007
Barometer's falling,
temperature's dropping.

712
00:59:51,043 --> 00:59:53,011
Dan, what is it?

713
00:59:53,045 --> 00:59:54,444
What the hell's that?

714
00:59:54,479 --> 00:59:56,174
Dan, what is it?
What's happening?

715
00:59:56,215 --> 00:59:58,683
What is it?
What's happening?

716
00:59:58,717 --> 01:00:01,185
Someone's shining a light
through the window.

717
01:00:01,220 --> 01:00:02,517
Dan, listen to me.

718
01:00:02,554 --> 01:00:05,387
Hold on, sweetheart.
I want to check this out.

719
01:00:08,227 --> 01:00:11,355
Dan, stay on the phone!

720
01:00:22,808 --> 01:00:24,708
This has got to be a joke.

721
01:00:29,681 --> 01:00:32,206
Someone's at the front door,
sweetheart...

722
01:00:32,251 --> 01:00:34,116
playing a stupid joke.

723
01:00:34,152 --> 01:00:36,848
And whoever it is...

724
01:00:36,888 --> 01:00:39,186
they ain't gonna like
finding me home.

725
01:00:39,224 --> 01:00:41,021
Dan, stay away from the door!

726
01:00:57,909 --> 01:00:59,206
Anybody here?

727
01:01:02,714 --> 01:01:05,012
Some asshole got drunk
and started taking...

728
01:01:05,050 --> 01:01:07,814
this 100-year-old business
too seriously.

729
01:02:00,772 --> 01:02:04,833
And so all of us living here
in Antonio Bay today...

730
01:02:04,876 --> 01:02:07,003
owe a great debt
of gratitude...

731
01:02:07,045 --> 01:02:09,479
to those men and women
a hundred years ago...

732
01:02:09,514 --> 01:02:12,677
who struggled and sacrificed
to make this town grow...

733
01:02:12,718 --> 01:02:14,413
into what it is today.

734
01:02:14,453 --> 01:02:18,913
And it's up to us to keep
their kind of spirit alive.

735
01:02:23,895 --> 01:02:25,123
I have an urgent bulletin.

736
01:02:25,163 --> 01:02:28,894
Will Sheriff David Simms please
contact KAB Radio immediately?

737
01:02:28,934 --> 01:02:31,994
The number is 555-2131.

738
01:02:32,037 --> 01:02:33,766
This is an emergency.

739
01:02:35,941 --> 01:02:40,275
So we must redouble our efforts,
work together.

740
01:02:40,312 --> 01:02:42,837
We have a vital,
thriving community.

741
01:02:42,881 --> 01:02:45,349
And I say
we have to keep it that way.

742
01:02:48,487 --> 01:02:50,421
This is an emergency.

743
01:02:50,455 --> 01:02:53,913
Sheriff David Simms,
please contact KAB immediately.

744
01:02:53,959 --> 01:02:57,690
555-2131.
This is an emergency.

745
01:03:12,844 --> 01:03:14,038
Sheriff Simms?

746
01:03:20,018 --> 01:03:21,849
And so, as we make our way...

747
01:03:21,887 --> 01:03:23,548
to the presentation
of the statue...

748
01:03:23,588 --> 01:03:25,886
I think we should all
keep in mind...

749
01:03:25,924 --> 01:03:27,516
the significance
of this night...

750
01:03:27,559 --> 01:03:29,891
for every citizen
of Antonio Bay.

751
01:04:18,109 --> 01:04:21,875
We should all proceed
over to the statue.

752
01:04:21,913 --> 01:04:23,972
Single file. Don't push.

753
01:04:24,015 --> 01:04:25,607
Take your time.

754
01:04:51,843 --> 01:04:53,811
Start!

755
01:04:53,845 --> 01:04:55,836
Please start!

756
01:05:00,218 --> 01:05:01,981
Why did all the lights go out?

757
01:05:02,020 --> 01:05:06,957
One of the lines
are probably down, Andy.

758
01:05:06,992 --> 01:05:10,689
They usually take care
of these things right away.

759
01:05:10,729 --> 01:05:13,425
I think it's kind of neat.

760
01:05:40,725 --> 01:05:42,590
What's that now?

761
01:05:59,144 --> 01:06:00,668
Start!

762
01:06:06,418 --> 01:06:08,818
Andy! Andy,
get out of the house!

763
01:06:08,853 --> 01:06:11,185
Mrs. Kobritz, get him
out of the house! Please! Run!

764
01:06:11,222 --> 01:06:14,157
I think maybe we better
close all the windows, Andy.

765
01:06:14,192 --> 01:06:15,887
Are your bedroom windows
closed?

766
01:06:15,927 --> 01:06:17,189
I'll go see.

767
01:06:26,071 --> 01:06:28,505
Someone listen to me!
My son is trapped!

768
01:06:28,540 --> 01:06:31,509
887 White Beach Lane!
My son is trapped by the fog!

769
01:06:31,543 --> 01:06:33,841
Andy, get out of the house!
Run!

770
01:06:38,383 --> 01:06:41,409
Wow! Look at that!

771
01:06:41,453 --> 01:06:43,216
Are your windows all closed?

772
01:06:43,254 --> 01:06:44,585
Yes, ma'am.

773
01:06:44,623 --> 01:06:46,181
What about
your mother's bedroom?

774
01:06:57,936 --> 01:07:00,996
Please, someone!
My son is trapped!

775
01:07:03,575 --> 01:07:05,475
Andy, run! Run!

776
01:07:05,510 --> 01:07:07,774
Mrs. Kobritz, run!

777
01:07:10,815 --> 01:07:13,613
Andy, I want you
to go to your room.

778
01:07:13,652 --> 01:07:15,210
I think I should stay.

779
01:07:15,253 --> 01:07:17,619
- Right now.
- Yes.

780
01:07:38,677 --> 01:07:39,905
Go to your room.

781
01:07:39,944 --> 01:07:41,605
I want to see who it is.

782
01:07:43,014 --> 01:07:45,039
Can't I stay
for two more seconds?

783
01:07:48,019 --> 01:07:50,647
OK, I'm going.

784
01:08:04,502 --> 01:08:06,493
Mrs. Kobritz?

785
01:08:16,548 --> 01:08:18,880
Please. My son is trapped!

786
01:08:18,917 --> 01:08:22,819
887 White Beach Lane.

787
01:08:22,854 --> 01:08:25,448
Someone get
to 887 White Beach Lane.

788
01:08:38,203 --> 01:08:42,003
My son is trapped!
Get him out of the fog!

789
01:08:48,713 --> 01:08:50,704
Please, someone!

790
01:08:51,983 --> 01:08:53,541
My son is trapped!

791
01:09:02,494 --> 01:09:04,394
Come on!
Get out of there, now!

792
01:09:13,271 --> 01:09:15,967
Andy, run! Run!

793
01:09:18,576 --> 01:09:20,441
Come on! Come on.

794
01:09:20,478 --> 01:09:22,241
Go! Go!

795
01:09:34,526 --> 01:09:35,788
Come on!

796
01:09:35,827 --> 01:09:39,092
Don't pop it.
Try to ease it out.

797
01:09:39,130 --> 01:09:40,688
Oh, Jesus.

798
01:09:46,771 --> 01:09:48,329
Come on, baby!

799
01:09:48,373 --> 01:09:51,831
Come on. It'll go.

800
01:09:51,876 --> 01:09:53,036
Reverse! Reverse!

801
01:09:53,077 --> 01:09:54,510
Come on!

802
01:10:01,553 --> 01:10:03,418
Come on, do it! Do it!

803
01:10:28,379 --> 01:10:30,404
...Stevie Wayne
for the last twenty minutes.

804
01:10:30,615 --> 01:10:32,879
I think it's best
we call it a night here.

805
01:10:32,917 --> 01:10:34,384
Another five or ten minutes...

806
01:10:34,419 --> 01:10:36,216
everyone will have
seen the statue.

807
01:10:36,254 --> 01:10:38,722
All right, but let's get them
through as quickly as we can.

808
01:10:38,756 --> 01:10:41,224
Probably be a good idea
if you went home, Kathy.

809
01:10:41,259 --> 01:10:42,886
We can close up here.

810
01:10:42,927 --> 01:10:44,224
I should see it through
to the end.

811
01:10:44,262 --> 01:10:46,560
Mrs. Williams,
there's nothing more to do here.

812
01:10:46,598 --> 01:10:48,964
Let me take you home.

813
01:10:49,000 --> 01:10:51,833
A little annoying,
but you're right.

814
01:10:51,870 --> 01:10:53,997
- Would you please take me?
- Yes, ma'am.

815
01:10:54,038 --> 01:10:56,700
- I'll call you tomorrow.
- Thank you.

816
01:11:01,446 --> 01:11:03,812
Andy, I don't even know
if you can hear me.

817
01:11:03,848 --> 01:11:05,941
I'm sorry that
I didn't come for you...

818
01:11:05,984 --> 01:11:07,144
that I wasn't there.

819
01:11:08,553 --> 01:11:11,044
Andy, please understand.

820
01:11:12,891 --> 01:11:15,724
I have to stay here.

821
01:11:26,671 --> 01:11:30,937
The fog is moving inland...

822
01:11:30,975 --> 01:11:32,875
away from the beach...

823
01:11:35,480 --> 01:11:37,414
towards Antonio Bay.

824
01:11:43,388 --> 01:11:45,549
It's over by the armory.

825
01:11:45,590 --> 01:11:48,320
I can't remember the name.

826
01:11:48,359 --> 01:11:51,157
No, no...
I think it's Chestnut.

827
01:11:55,934 --> 01:11:58,994
Feel like listening
to some music?

828
01:11:59,037 --> 01:12:01,528
Sure.

829
01:12:01,572 --> 01:12:03,437
It's moving faster now.

830
01:12:03,474 --> 01:12:04,964
Up Regent Avenue.

831
01:12:05,009 --> 01:12:07,000
Up to the end
of Smallhouse Road.

832
01:12:07,045 --> 01:12:08,478
What is that?

833
01:12:11,182 --> 01:12:13,742
It's just hitting
the outskirts of town.

834
01:12:13,785 --> 01:12:15,776
Broad Street.

835
01:12:17,221 --> 01:12:19,712
Clay Street.

836
01:12:46,084 --> 01:12:47,915
It's moving down 10th Street.

837
01:12:47,952 --> 01:12:51,410
Get inside and lock your doors.
Close your windows.

838
01:12:51,456 --> 01:12:53,686
There's something in the fog.

839
01:13:00,264 --> 01:13:02,596
If you're on the south side
of town, go north.

840
01:13:02,633 --> 01:13:04,601
Stay away from the fog.

841
01:13:13,011 --> 01:13:15,104
Richardsville Pike
up to Beacon Hill...

842
01:13:15,146 --> 01:13:17,512
is the only clear road.

843
01:13:17,548 --> 01:13:19,516
Up to the church.

844
01:13:19,550 --> 01:13:22,644
If you can get out of town,
get to the old church.

845
01:13:30,495 --> 01:13:32,929
Now the junction at 101
is cut off.

846
01:13:32,964 --> 01:13:36,422
If you can get out of town,
get to the old church.

847
01:13:36,467 --> 01:13:38,367
It's the only place
left to go.

848
01:13:38,403 --> 01:13:41,236
Get to the old church
on Beacon Hill.

849
01:13:49,414 --> 01:13:51,211
- It cut us off!
- Where is it?

850
01:13:51,249 --> 01:13:52,978
- Right behind us.
- Quick, inside.

851
01:13:56,454 --> 01:13:58,149
Come on.

852
01:13:58,189 --> 01:13:59,349
Hurry.

853
01:14:01,225 --> 01:14:04,160
Father, is there a basement
or cellar in here?

854
01:14:04,195 --> 01:14:06,220
- We can't hide any longer.
- We have to try!

855
01:14:06,264 --> 01:14:08,198
No matter where we go,
it will find us.

856
01:14:12,637 --> 01:14:14,332
Is there a basement
or cellar here?

857
01:14:14,372 --> 01:14:16,340
There's a study in back.
I'll show you the way.

858
01:14:16,374 --> 01:14:17,807
Come on. Hurry.

859
01:14:17,842 --> 01:14:20,208
Give me that.

860
01:14:49,273 --> 01:14:51,207
The fog is sweeping inland.

861
01:14:52,710 --> 01:14:55,543
It's almost like a wall
across the east end of town.

862
01:15:20,138 --> 01:15:22,003
Blake and his men
have come for us.

863
01:15:22,039 --> 01:15:23,631
- Who's Blake?
- It's in the journal.

864
01:15:23,674 --> 01:15:24,800
- What journal?
- I don't know.

865
01:15:24,842 --> 01:15:27,140
- We're cursed.
- What are you talking about?

866
01:15:27,178 --> 01:15:30,375
- Where is the journal?
- It's in there.

867
01:15:36,454 --> 01:15:37,785
Over by the window?

868
01:15:37,822 --> 01:15:40,848
- It can do us no good now.
- It's all we got.

869
01:15:40,892 --> 01:15:42,587
If anything happens,
just lock the door.

870
01:15:42,627 --> 01:15:44,959
Get back. Shut the door.

871
01:16:25,203 --> 01:16:26,397
''Six must die.''

872
01:16:26,437 --> 01:16:27,699
The three men
on the ''Sea Grass''.

873
01:16:27,738 --> 01:16:29,330
And the weatherman is four.

874
01:16:29,373 --> 01:16:30,840
- Mrs. Kobritz.
- Yeah, five.

875
01:16:30,875 --> 01:16:32,342
And one of us makes six.

876
01:16:32,376 --> 01:16:34,003
That's what they want.
They've come back...

877
01:16:34,045 --> 01:16:35,672
for the six
original conspirators.

878
01:16:35,713 --> 01:16:37,146
There must be something
in here!

879
01:16:37,181 --> 01:16:38,671
It's me they want.
I am the sixth!

880
01:16:38,716 --> 01:16:39,842
Why would they want you?

881
01:16:39,884 --> 01:16:41,181
Wait, Father.
You didn't read us this.

882
01:16:41,219 --> 01:16:43,187
''Were it possible
to raise the dead...

883
01:16:43,221 --> 01:16:45,519
''I would return Blake's fortune
to him intact...

884
01:16:45,556 --> 01:16:48,491
''save the money spent
on these walls that hide it.''

885
01:16:48,526 --> 01:16:50,426
''My fellow conspirators
believe...

886
01:16:50,461 --> 01:16:52,452
''that the confiscated fortune
has been stolen...

887
01:16:52,496 --> 01:16:55,124
''from them, when in fact,
I am the thief...

888
01:16:55,166 --> 01:16:57,634
''and God's temple
is the tomb of gold.''

889
01:16:57,668 --> 01:17:01,195
''I am the thief,
and God's temple... ''

890
01:17:03,074 --> 01:17:05,269
Now, wait. Get rid of that.

891
01:17:06,877 --> 01:17:09,437
Get out of the way!

892
01:17:30,568 --> 01:17:34,004
- Give me a hand.
- Andy, stay right there.

893
01:17:57,695 --> 01:17:59,390
The gold.

894
01:18:18,316 --> 01:18:20,614
He melted down the gold
into this.

895
01:18:24,689 --> 01:18:26,554
Somebody help her!

896
01:18:39,704 --> 01:18:41,467
Don't go in there!

897
01:19:22,380 --> 01:19:25,247
Blake, I have your gold.

898
01:19:32,656 --> 01:19:33,816
Blake?

899
01:20:11,896 --> 01:20:13,830
This is your gold, Blake.

900
01:20:13,864 --> 01:20:17,231
My grandfather stole it
from you.

901
01:20:19,270 --> 01:20:22,068
I'm the one
who must answer for it.

902
01:20:34,752 --> 01:20:37,744
I'm the sixth conspirator.

903
01:20:39,757 --> 01:20:42,885
I'm Father Malone.

904
01:20:42,927 --> 01:20:45,088
Take me.

905
01:21:41,452 --> 01:21:43,249
Father Malone!

906
01:24:02,926 --> 01:24:04,291
Look.

907
01:24:14,538 --> 01:24:16,199
It's going away.

908
01:24:52,176 --> 01:24:55,612
I don't know what happened
to Antonio Bay tonight.

909
01:24:55,646 --> 01:24:58,979
Something came out of the fog...

910
01:24:59,016 --> 01:25:01,917
and tried to destroy us.

911
01:25:01,952 --> 01:25:04,978
In one moment, it vanished.

912
01:25:05,022 --> 01:25:08,514
But if this has been
anything but a nightmare...

913
01:25:08,559 --> 01:25:12,427
and if we don't wake up to find
ourselves safe in our beds...

914
01:25:12,463 --> 01:25:16,229
it could come again.

915
01:25:16,266 --> 01:25:19,702
To the ships at sea
who can hear my voice...

916
01:25:19,737 --> 01:25:23,969
look across the water
into the darkness.

917
01:25:25,375 --> 01:25:27,536
Look for the fog.

918
01:25:56,039 --> 01:25:59,167
Why not six, Blake?

919
01:26:01,678 --> 01:26:03,771
Why not me?

920
